This paper is about neural network training, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper specifically focuses on feedforward networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. The use of differential geometry and mathematical principles also suggests a potential fit for the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
